# Interface Research: Figma & Paper.design â†’ Ditter Gravity Studio

> Research compiled 2026-02-28 Â· Reference: Ditter.io (`App.jsx`, `index.css`)

---

## 1. Executive Summary

Ditter Gravity Studio is a physics-driven, dithering creative canvas. Both **Figma** (the industry-standard infinite canvas design tool) and **Paper.design** (a next-gen HTML/CSS-native design tool with built-in shader effects) represent the state of the art in creative canvas UX. This document distills the most relevant patterns from each and maps them to concrete improvements for our product.

---

## 2. Figma UI3 â€” Key Patterns

Figma's **UI3 redesign (Config 2024)** represents the most significant shift in creative tool UX in recent years.

### 2.1 Layout Architecture

```
â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¬â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”¬â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚  Left    â”‚                                 â”‚   Right      â”‚
â”‚  Panel   â”‚        Infinite Canvas          â”‚   Panel      â”‚
â”‚  Layers  â”‚                                 â”‚  Properties  â”‚
â”‚  Assets  â”‚   â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”      â”‚  Fills       â”‚
â”‚          â”‚   â”‚  Floating Toolbar    â”‚      â”‚  Effects     â”‚
â”‚          â”‚   â”‚    (bottom center)   â”‚      â”‚  Layout      â”‚
â”‚          â”‚   â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜      â”‚              â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”´â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”´â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜
                        â†‘
              Canvas-maximizing design
```

**Key layout principles:**

- **Dual sidebar architecture** â€” Left for structure/layers, Right for properties/controls
- **Floating toolbar at the bottom** â€” Frees canvas real estate; contains only active tools
- **Resizable & collapsible panels** â€” `[Tab]` hides all UI for full-canvas focus
- **Context-sensitive right panel** â€” Content changes based on what's selected

### 2.2 Navigation & Zoom

| Action            | Shortcut                             |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Pan canvas        | `Space` + Drag, or Middle Mouse Drag |
| Zoom in/out       | `Ctrl/Cmd` + Scroll                  |
| Fit to canvas     | `Shift+1`                            |
| Zoom to selection | `Shift+2`                            |
| Zoom 100%         | `Shift+0`                            |
| Box zoom          | Hold `Z`, drag                       |
| Select tool       | `V`                                  |
| Hand/Pan tool     | `H`                                  |
| Frame tool        | `A`                                  |

**Zoom display:** Always visible in bottom-right corner, clickable for custom input.

### 2.3 Canvas Experience

- **Infinite scrollable canvas** â€” No bounding box; world extends infinitely in all directions
- **Dynamic pixel grid** â€” Appears at zoom â‰¥ 800% (similar to ~8Ã— in our codebase)
- **Snap to pixel** â€” All coordinates snap to integer world-pixels
- **Multi-select** â€” Rubber-band select with drag
- **Middle mouse** â€” Always pans regardless of active tool

### 2.4 Toolbar Design (UI3)

The bottom-center floating toolbar contains:

```
[Move] [Scale] [Frame] [Section] [Rectangle] [Ellipse] [Pen] [Pencil] [Text] | [Comment] [Plugins]
```

- Tool icons are **monochrome SVG**, 16Ã—16
- Active tool gets a **subtle background pill highlight**
- Keyboard shortcut shown on hover tooltip
- Separator `|` groups related tools

### 2.5 Properties Panel (Right)

- **Collapsible sections** with animated expand/collapse
- Section headers are always visible even when collapsed
- **Color chips** are interactive, open a picker popover
- **Typography controls** use inline editing on click
- Fill, Stroke, Effect, Export â€” all as collapsible accordion rows

---

## 3. Paper.design â€” Key Patterns

Paper.design is a newer tool that positions itself as **HTML/CSS-native**, which makes it especially relevant for Ditter.io given our web export pipeline.

### 3.1 Unique Differentiators

| Feature                     | Paper.design                          | Relevance to Ditter.io                                  |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Built-in Shader effects** | GLSL shader overlays on any element   | Direct analogy to our dithering effects pipeline        |
| **Flex/layout engine**      | "Wrap in Flex" for responsive layouts | Useful for exported asset compositions                  |
| **HTML/CSS canvas**         | Designs ARE the code                  | Informs our "Copy to Figma" / export strategy           |
| **AI image generation**     | ChatGPT, Ideogram, Flux built-in      | Possible future AI upload prompt feature                |
| **Effect property panel**   | Shader parameters exposed as sliders  | Direct model for our Pixel Scale / Contrast / Effect UI |
| **Dev Mode**                | Export production-ready CSS           | Analogy to our SVG Export + Figma Copy                  |

### 3.2 Shader/Effect Panel Pattern

Paper.design exposes shader parameters through **structured property groups**:

```
â–¾ Shader Effects
  Type    â—‹ Overlay  â— Texture  â—‹ Animated
  Opacity â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â—â”€â”€â”€â”€ 78%
  Scale   â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â—â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ 4px
  Noise   â”€â”€â—â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€ 0.3

  [Preview Shader]
```

This is the **exact pattern** we should adopt for our Effect Engine â€” grouped sliders, live preview, labeled presets.

### 3.3 Interface Layout

- **Minimal top bar** â€” Just file name, share, and zoom %. No tool clutter at top
- **Floating right panel** â€” Properties follow the selected element
- **No persistent left panel** â€” Layers accessed via a pop-out sheet
- **Canvas fills entire screen** â€” Maximum creative real estate

