### 5.4 Keyboard Shortcuts to Add

| Key                 | Action                          |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| `H`                 | Hand/Pan tool                   |
| `V`                 | Select/Move tool                |
| `Tab`               | Toggle hide/show all UI panels  |
| `?`                 | Show keyboard shortcuts overlay |
| `Shift+0`           | Zoom to 100%                    |
| `Ctrl+-` / `Ctrl+=` | Zoom out / in                   |
| `Middle mouse drag` | Always pan                      |

### 5.5 Dark Mode

Both Figma and Paper.design support dark mode. Ditter.io's current brutalist palette (white `#e5e5e5` + black `#000`) maps cleanly to:

| Token             | Light     | Dark      |
| ----------------- | --------- | --------- |
| `--bg-color`      | `#e5e5e5` | `#111111` |
| `--text-color`    | `#000000` | `#f0f0f0` |
| `--border-color`  | `#000000` | `#333333` |
| `--surface-color` | `#ffffff` | `#1a1a1a` |
| `--accent-blue`   | `#0000ff` | `#4444ff` |

---

## 6. What NOT to Copy

Learning from user backlash on Figma's UI3:

- **Don't float the sidepanels** â€” Fixed-position panels are more reliable
- **Don't remove keyboard shortcuts** in favor of mouse-only flows
- **Don't over-AI** the interface â€” Our product's creative effects are the star, not AI suggestions
- **Don't copy Paper.design's minimal layers panel** â€” We need layers visibility for physics objects

---

